<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States and Britain are asking
transportation officials from 33 nations to work together on ways to
fight terrorism following last month's bombing of Pan Am Flight 103.
   The two countries on Tuesday proposed a meeting in Montreal next
month to that would seek improved international standards for
handling passengers, baggage and cargo to prevent sabotage, said
