<HEAD>Fighter Jet Clips Ski Lift Cable, Lands Safely</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRENOBLE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ski lift at l'Alpe de Huez will be
closed several days for repairs after a low-flying French air force
fighter clipped the cable, police said today.
   The Mirage 2000 fighter, flying at about 430 m.p.h., hit the lift
cable Tuesday at about 5 p.m., after the ski lift in southeastern
France had stopped operating for the day.
   The pilot was able to land safely at the nearby military base of
St. Etienne de St. Geoir, authorities reported. No one was hurt, but
several strands of the cable were severed.
