<SECOND>PM-SAfrica-Hospitals,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Medical School Dean Urges Integration of White Hospitals</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dean of South Africa's
largest medical school said today that two whites-only hospitals
should be opened to black patients to ease overcrowding in Soweto.
   Professor Clive Rosendorf, dean of the faculty of medicine at the
University of the Witwatersrand in Johannesburg, said the occupancy
rate at Soweto's Baragwanath Hospital has been 155 percent, with
many patients sleeping on the floor.
   Baragwanath is the only full-service hospital in the black
township of 2.5 million people.
   Rosendorf said more beds should be provided at Baragwanath, but
he also recommended that black patients be admitted to two major
white hospitals in the region _ Johannesburg Hospital and South Rand
Hospital.
   All public hospitals in South Africa are racially segregated, as
are residential areas and government-run schools.
