   Bush wants to be known as the ``education president.'' That costs
money.
   His ``kinder, gentler nation'' that addresses the homeless, AIDS,
children, ... affordable housing, etc. has a hefty price tag too.
   A teetering savings and loan industry must be shored up, and that
won't be cheap. ...
   But it will be hard for us to rally around a breeze. Bush's call
for bipartisanship, however, is another matter. If he produces
results from a warmer relationship, that's someting Americans can
embrace.
</TEXT>
