<FIRST>r a AM-BellevueMurder     01-25 0290</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bellevue Murder,0297</SECOND>
<HEAD>Homeless Man Indicted in Murder of Doctor at NYC Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homeless man who lived in a secluded part of a
hospital and was arrested in the murder of a physician there has
been indicted by a grand jury, the prosecutor said Wednesday.
   District Attorney Robert Morgenthau said Steven Smith beat,
raped, sodomized, strangled and robbed Dr. Kathryn Hinnant in her
fourth-floor office at Bellevue Hospital on Jan. 7.
   Her husband and a hospital administrator found her body the next
day, and Smith was arrested Jan. 9 after three homeless men said he
gave them items belonging to the doctor to sell.
   A $30,000 reward was offered in the case. Morgenthau said the
award money would be claimed, but declined to say by whom.
   Smith, 23, was charged with two counts of second-degree murder _
one accusing him of intentionally killing her, the other charging
that he caused her death while committing other felonies. The
maximum sentence in either case is 25 years to life. He was also
indicted on charges of first-degree robbery, rape and sodomy.
   Smith is being held without bail and will be arraigned in about
10 days, Morgenthau said. When arrested, Smith admitted being at the
murder scene but said another homeless man, whom he identified only
as John, killed Hinnant.
   ``We have nothing to corroborate his statement that anyone else
was involved,'' Morgenthau said.
   Smith lived in a maintenance and storage space on the 22nd floor
of the vast hospital at least since before Christmas, police said.
   Morgenthau said Smith stole the doctor's fur coat. He also
removed a ring, bracelets and a watch from her body, but did not
take them with him, the prosecutor said.
</TEXT>
