<HEAD>Former Phoenix Suns Basketball Player Convicted of Killing Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former professional basketball player
Michael Donnell Niles faces the death penalty for killing his wife
to collect on her $100,000 insurance policy.
   Niles was convicted Tuesday in the Dec. 13, 1984, death of Sonja
