<FIRST>r w AM-TreasuryAuction     01-25 0088</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Treasury Auction,80</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in
Wednesday's auction to the lowest level since November.
   The average yield was 9.08 percent, down from 9.23 percent at the
last auction on Dec. 28.
   It was the lowest rate since two-year notes averaged 8.88 percent
on Nov. 22. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 9 percent
with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,985.70.
   A total of $9.29 billion in notes were sold out of bids totalling
$26.0 billion.
