<FIRST>r a AM-SchoolBus     01-25 0244</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-School Bus,0255</SECOND>
<HEAD>Driver, Pupil Killed When Bus Rolls Into Creek</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OTTAWA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus skidded off a muddy country road
and overturned into a creek Wednesday, killing the driver and a
child despite the efforts of a 16-year-old boy who tossed children
to safety as the bus sank.
   Bill Raley, a sophomore at Wellsville High School who was one of
12 students on the bus, said the bus was upside down in the water
and `` I just started grabbing them and throwing them out the door.''
   Dale R. Thomasson, 46, a teacher, counselor and school bus
driver, and Loren Newkirk II, 8, drowned in the accident,
authorities said.
   Raley ``went back to get the (8-year-old) kid and the bus rolled
again. He jumped out and they said they never saw the driver or the
other kid again,'' said Alan Radcliffe, a Franklin County deputy
sheriff.
   Police said the two victims, both from Wellsville in rural
east-central Kansas, were trapped under the bus in Walnut Creek for
more than an hour before wreckers recovered the vehicle.
   Newkirk was pronounced dead four hours later at an Ottawa
hospital.
   Radcliffe said the bus was en route to school, about seven miles
northeast of Ottawa when it slowed for a curve but ran off the road
after the turn because of muddy conditions.
   The bus then slid onto the bridge over Walnut Creek and rolled
into five or six feet of water.
