has told Congress unless economic growth slows, the nation ``would
risk a serious intensification of inflationary pressures at some not
too distant point.''
   Greenspan, testifying before the House Banking Committee on
Tuesday, said it was ``especially encouraging'' the economy managed
to grow at a strong pace last year without a flare-up of inflation,
but mounting pressures on prices will keep the central bank's
monetary policy on the tight side.
