a $3.2 billion hostile buyout offer from Shamrock Holdings Inc.,
setting the stage for a threatened proxy fight for control of
Polaroid.
   Shamrock, a television and radio concern owned by the Roy E.
Disney family, last week increased its offer to $45 per share for
all Polaroid stock, including 9.7 million shares issued under
Polaroid's controversial employee stock ownership plan.
   In a statement Tuesday, Polaroid called the latest sweetened
offer ``inadequate from a financial point of view and not in the
best interest of Polaroid and its stockholders, except Shamrock and
