<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Phone     01-25 0241</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Phone,0249</SECOND>
<HEAD>Quarterly Earnings Up 6.5 Percent At U S West, 6.2 Percent At Bell
Atlantic</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Two of the regional Bell holding companies on Wednesday reported
higher profits in the fourth quarter, a 6.5 percent gain at U S West
Inc. and a 6.2 percent rise at Bell Atlantic Corp.
   Denver-based U S West, which provides local phone service in
western and northwestern states, said its earnings rose to $271.7
million, or $1.49 a share, from $255 million, or $1.35 a share, a
year earlier. Revenue rose 1.1 percent to $2.35 billion from $2.32
billion.
   For the full year, U S West said its earnings rose 12.6 percent
to $1.13 billion, or $6.17 a share, from $1.01 billion, or $5.31 a
share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 6 percent to $9.22 billion from
$8.7 billion.
   The 1988 results included a one-time gain of $89 million from the
second-quarter sale of shares by the company's cellular and paging
subsidiary, U S West NewVector Group Inc.
   Philadelphia-based Bell Atlantic, which serves mid-Atlantic
states, said its earnings rose in the quarter to $302.6 million, or
$1.53 a share, from $285 million, or $1.44 a share, a year earlier.
Revenue rose 1.8 percent to $2.77 billion from $2.72 billion.
   For the full year, profit rose to $1.32 billion, or $6.65 a
share, from $1.24 billion, or $6.24 a share, a year earlier. Revenue
rose to $10.9 billion from $10.7 billion.

</TEXT>
