<FIRST>r f BC-BeerMarket     01-25 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Beer Market,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Miller Continues Slide As Anheuser-Busch Remains No. 1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anheuser-Busch Cos. Inc. solidified its grip on
the nation's beer market last year while Miller Brewing Co. saw its
flagship brand slip from the ranks of the top five, according to an
industry newsletter.
   Anheuser-Busch, based in St. Louis, continued to hold the top
spot in beer shipments, with its Budweiser brand in the lead at 50.4
million barrels last year, an increase over 49.5 million in 1987,
according to Beer Marketer's Insights.
   Anheuser-Busch's Bud Light made gains on Miller's Lite beer, the
No. 2 brand in the country. Lite had shipments of 19.3 million
barrels in 1988, but Bud Light grew by 18 percent to 9.7 million
barrels to grab the No. 3 ranking.
   Coors Light, a product of the Adolph Coors Co. of Golden, Colo.,
had shipments of 8.9 million barrels, making it the No. 4 brand.
   Anheuser-Busch's Busch brand came in No. 5 at 8.65 million
barrels.
   Miller High Life, the flagship brand of the Milwaukee-based
brewer, had been ranked No. 3 in the country in 1987. But the brand
dropped to sixth in 1988 at 8.35 million barrels.
   The figures were reported this week by the newsletter, based in
West Nyack, N.Y.
</TEXT>
