<HEAD>London Shares Close Mixed</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with later activity, closing index;
No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices finished narrowly mixed Wednesday, as
players took advantage of the market's recent surge to take some
profits ahead of Friday's scheduled release of British trade figures.
   Prices soared in heavy early trading following Wall Street's
gains Tuesday, pushing the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share
index to its best level since the October 1987 stock crash.
   But prices began to decline on profit-taking in the afternoon, a
trend that picked up momentum as the day drew to a close.
   The 100-share index finished with a loss of 2.1 points, or 0.1
percent, at 1,939.0, just 2 points above its worst level for the
day, reached at late afternoon. The index rallied as much as 26
points in early trading.
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended with a slight gain of
0.1 point at 1,580.8, reflecting stronger performances in some of
the major stocks.
   The Financial Times 500-share index fell 0.35 point to 1,092.64
at the close.
   Volume reached a hefty 924.7 million shares, up from 562.8
million shares Tuesday.
