<FIRST>u f AM-DuPontBuyback     01-25 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Du Pont Buyback,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>Du Pont Board Authorizes Purchase of 20 Million Shares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Du Pont Co.'s board of directors on
Wednesday authorized the purchase of up to 20 million shares of
common stock in an effort to improve the stock's value, the company
announced.
   At the current value of Du Pont stock, the purchase would be
worth around $2 billion. The proposed purchase represents about 8
percent of the company's common shares.
   Du Pont's stock rose $2.12{ to $98.50 a share Wednesday in
consolidated New York Stock Exchange trading.
   The board also declared a first-quarter dividend of $1.05 per
share on outstanding common stock, an increase of 10 cents from the
dividend paid in the fourth quarter of 1988. The dividend was last
raised nine months ago.
   Under the repurchasing program, shares will be bought on the open
market, or through privately negotiated transactions, at prevailing
market rates from time to time.
   ``This buyback program is another step in our efforts to improve
the overall return to shareholders without jeopardizing our
financial strength or sacrificing growth opportunities that may
present themselves,'' said Chairman Richard E. Heckert.
   As of Dec. 31, 1988, Du Pont had 239.4 million shares of common
stock outstanding.
