<FIRST>r f AM-Eastern-Brazil     01-25 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Eastern-Brazil,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eastern Announces New Brazilian Routes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eastern Airlines said Wednesday it planned to start
daily, non-stop flights between Miami and the Brazilian cities of
Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo later this year.
   The airline said a new bilateral accord between the United States
and Brazil would also give the Miami-based carrier the right to
serve the Brazilian cities of Brasilia, Manaus, Recife and Porto
Alegre.
   Eastern also is to increase its weekly flights between New York
and Brazilian destinations from seven to 10 in 1991.
   Miami-based Eastern is the largest U.S. carrier to Central and
South America, serving 18 cities in 14 countries with some 90
flights per week.
</TEXT>
